# Cursor Rules
# This file contains rules for the Cursor AI assistant.

# Project Context
# - The project uses CMake for build configuration.
# - The project uses C++20 standard.
# - The build directory is `_build`.

# Coding Style
# - Use C++ for backend/native code.

# Documentation
# - Add comments for complex logic.

# Directory Structure
# - Place third-party configuration in `thirdparty/` (find_package for vcpkg ports; Clipper2 FetchContent lives under edgar).
# - Place project source code in:
#   - `src/apps/` for applications.
#   - `src/libs/` for shared libraries.
#   - `src/tests/` for tests (enable_testing + add_subdirectory in root CMakeLists).

# Build Instructions
# - Use `build_vs.bat` to run `cmake --preset vs2026` and `cmake --build --preset debug` (see CMakePresets.json).
# - CMake build output goes to `_build/`.
# - Executables are located in `_build/bin/Debug/` (or Release).
# - vcpkg packages (ImGui, SDL3, etc.) are linked statically via the manifest + x64-windows-static triplet.

# Dependencies
# - SDL3, ImGui, Boost, etc. come from the vcpkg manifest (`vcpkg.json`); installed under
#   `_build/vcpkg_installed/` when configuring with the vcpkg toolchain (see `build_vs.bat`).
# - `thirdparty/CMakeLists.txt` uses find_package(SDL3), find_package(imgui); static linking
#   matches triplet `x64-windows-static` in CMakePresets.json.
# - Clipper2 is FetchContent inside `src/libs/edgar` (not vcpkg), built into `_build/_deps/`.

